HEADWORD: Florideæ
<hw>Flo*rid"e*⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from L. <ets>flos</ets>, <ets>floris</ets>, a flower.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A subclass of alg⟦ae⟧ including all the red or
purplish seaweeds; the <subclass>Rhodosperme⟦ae⟧</subclass> of many
authors; -- so called from the rosy or florid color of most of the
species.</def>⟦br⟧
